11:43.212 --> 11:44.612
Okay. Got it.

11:44.748 --> 11:47.615
None of this was making sense,
but it finally does.

11:47.617 --> 11:49.283
Is this a "sister act"
situation?

11:49.285 --> 11:50.684
If it is,
you have to tell me.

11:50.686 --> 11:52.353
Like from the movie
"sister act"

11:52.488 --> 11:53.955
With whoopi goldberg?

11:54.090 --> 11:56.624
Don't play dumb with me.
You know what "sister act" is.

11:56.626 --> 11:58.692
Are you insinuating
that I am just

11:58.828 --> 12:02.029
A fun and charismatic
performer

12:02.031 --> 12:05.499
Who is hiding out in a church
pretending to be clergy

12:05.635 --> 12:08.369
Because I witnessed a murder
carried out by the bingoni mob?

12:08.504 --> 12:09.771
Get real.
[ door bangs open ]

12:09.905 --> 12:12.173
Man: That's him!
The bingonis say hello!

12:12.308 --> 12:13.975
[ gunshot ]
[ gasps ]

12:14.110 --> 12:15.309
[ door slams ]

12:15.445 --> 12:17.579
Oh, my god!
Was this my fault?

12:17.713 --> 12:18.912
No. No!

12:18.914 --> 12:20.849
I can't be responsible
for everyone!

12:23.386 --> 12:25.853
Okay!
Good news and bad news.

12:25.989 --> 12:27.255
Uh, the good news is

12:27.390 --> 12:28.790
That someone
said hello to the pastor.

12:28.925 --> 12:31.593
The bad news is
it was a mob-style hello

12:31.727 --> 12:32.794
Where he got got.

12:32.928 --> 12:33.995
What?
He's gone.

12:34.130 --> 12:35.729
Gone where?!

12:35.731 --> 12:36.998
Heaven, I guess.

12:37.133 --> 12:39.667
Then I'm going
to heaven, too.

12:39.669 --> 12:41.135
Goodbye forever!

12:41.270 --> 12:42.403
Stop!

12:42.538 --> 12:44.405
Geez, I'm trying
to steer you,

12:44.540 --> 12:46.274
But you're like
a bad shopping cart

12:46.409 --> 12:48.009
That veers
right into the wall!

12:48.144 --> 12:49.410
I'm going to do it!

12:49.545 --> 12:51.078
Then you'll never
see him again!

12:51.080 --> 12:53.214
Because you can't go to heaven
if you kill yourself!

12:53.349 --> 12:55.683
Those pricks thought
of everything.

12:55.819 --> 12:57.485
Right! So...

12:57.487 --> 13:00.488
The only way to go to heaven
is to do what the pastor says

13:00.490 --> 13:02.890
And do good deeds --
lots and lots!

13:03.026 --> 13:06.160
So let's just keep you
very with the good deeds!

13:06.162 --> 13:08.696
You mean like mitzvahs?
I'm supposed to be jewish.

13:08.698 --> 13:09.697
Hold!

13:09.833 --> 13:11.165
"a mitzvah is...

13:11.300 --> 13:12.233
A good deed"!

13:12.368 --> 13:13.635
So, yes! Yes.

13:13.769 --> 13:15.703
Let's channel all
of that amazing, intense,

13:15.839 --> 13:19.507
Crazy girl energy
into the doing of mitzvahs!

13:19.509 --> 13:22.043
How's<i> that</i> for being
an adult woman?!

13:22.178 --> 13:27.648
♪♪

13:27.783 --> 13:33.855
♪♪

13:33.990 --> 13:35.256
Yep, I did this.

13:35.391 --> 13:36.724
We're doing
good work here.

13:36.726 --> 13:38.326
Oh, would you like
to help as well?

13:38.461 --> 13:39.593
No, she's doing
that part.

13:39.729 --> 13:41.262
I would love some
more soup, though.

13:41.397 --> 13:45.867
♪♪

13:46.001 --> 13:48.402
I brought her here,
emotionally and physically.

13:48.538 --> 13:50.804
Ah, it feels so good!

13:50.806 --> 13:51.805
Can I get some soup?

13:51.807 --> 13:54.475
Um...No.

13:56.345 --> 13:58.812
[ line ringing ]

13:58.948 --> 14:00.348
I fixed everything!

14:00.483 --> 14:01.683
I'm in a meeting.
I can't talk.

14:01.817 --> 14:03.951
Gilda hasn't mentioned
the pastor in months.

14:04.087 --> 14:07.288
And she's been named
female mensch of the year!

14:07.423 --> 14:08.956
Her mom would be
so happy.

14:09.092 --> 14:12.226
Listen, I'm very busy.
I'm pretending to be in japan.

14:12.228 --> 14:13.761
Pretending
to close a deal.

14:14.564 --> 14:15.897
[ applause ]

14:16.031 --> 14:18.966
Thank you so much
for recognizing me as

14:18.968 --> 14:20.234
Female mensch of the year.

14:20.369 --> 14:22.103
Whoo!

14:22.238 --> 14:23.971
Why do we do good deeds?

14:23.973 --> 14:26.373
Because it's our moral duty
to leave the world

14:26.375 --> 14:27.909
Better than we found it?

14:28.043 --> 14:28.910
No.

14:29.044 --> 14:30.444
[ belches loudly ]

14:30.446 --> 14:32.580
It's so we can just die already,
go to heaven,

14:32.582 --> 14:34.782
And do step three
with the hot pastor.

14:34.918 --> 14:37.851
My adult friend hayley
taught me all of this.

14:37.853 --> 14:40.521
But the thing is,
it's taking too long.

14:40.656 --> 14:42.790
So I found a loophole!

14:42.792 --> 14:45.927
Whatever the pastor knew,
I also know.

14:46.061 --> 14:47.729
I saw the bingonis...

14:47.863 --> 14:48.996
Do whatever.

14:48.998 --> 14:49.997
[ door bangs open ]

14:49.999 --> 14:51.198
Man: She knows too much!

14:51.334 --> 14:53.468
[ gunfire ]
[ crowd screaming ]

14:55.338 --> 14:56.804
Listen, we are
on the run now.

14:56.940 --> 14:59.807
So we gotta stay safe.
Yeah, I guess so.

14:59.809 --> 15:02.610
I'm too sleepy to talk.
Can you tell me a story?

15:02.745 --> 15:06.147
Yeah, sure.
Once upon a time...

15:06.282 --> 15:08.415
I thought
I was an adult.

15:08.417 --> 15:10.618
I tried to be there
for you, but...

15:10.620 --> 15:12.620
I just kept making
everything worse.

15:12.622 --> 15:14.688
Mm, this is
a bad story.

15:14.824 --> 15:16.223
[ snoring ]

15:16.359 --> 15:18.091
In a way,
you're roger,

15:18.093 --> 15:20.093
But you're also real.

15:20.095 --> 15:23.697
I will fix this.
I<i> will</i> take care of you.

15:23.833 --> 15:26.900
And no matter what,
I'll never let --

15:26.902 --> 15:28.569
[ snores ]

15:28.704 --> 15:30.638
...Them hurt you.
[ door bangs open ]

15:30.773 --> 15:32.840
Man: We know
to whom you are referring!

15:32.976 --> 15:33.908
[ gunshot ]

15:35.778 --> 15:37.444
[ wind rushing ]

15:41.984 --> 15:43.383
Where's gilda?

15:44.052 --> 15:45.385
Where am<i> I?</i>

15:45.520 --> 15:48.455
[ indistinct conversations,
laughter ]

15:55.930 --> 15:58.398
You must be hayley.
Welcome!

15:58.533 --> 15:59.866
This is for you.
Oh, okay.

16:00.002 --> 16:00.934
Picture's up!

16:04.139 --> 16:05.338
There's baby.

16:05.474 --> 16:06.939
That's baby's dad!

16:06.941 --> 16:07.874
Am I in the shot?

16:07.876 --> 16:09.609
No!
You're doing great!

16:09.744 --> 16:11.344
Roll sound,
roll camera.

16:11.346 --> 16:12.679
Hold for sound!

16:12.815 --> 16:14.648
Wait, is that the pastor?

16:15.750 --> 16:17.217
He dead.

16:17.352 --> 16:18.885
Am<i> I</i> dead?

16:19.021 --> 16:20.753
Hi, is this heaven?

16:20.755 --> 16:22.955
Or am I somehow
a boom mic operator

16:22.957 --> 16:24.424
On the set
of "dirty dancing"?

16:24.559 --> 16:26.226
All of the above!

16:26.361 --> 16:28.561
Heaven<i> is</i>
"dirty dancing."

16:28.697 --> 16:30.497
But more specifically,

16:30.632 --> 16:34.567
Heaven is the moment
on the set of "dirty dancing"

16:34.569 --> 16:37.170
When we,
the people behind the camera,

16:37.172 --> 16:40.773
Realize that we're making
something really special.

16:40.909 --> 16:43.310
Yeah,
that makes sense.

16:43.445 --> 16:45.178
Real quick --
are you god?

16:45.313 --> 16:46.179
Kind of!

16:46.314 --> 16:47.580
I'm emile ardolino,

16:47.582 --> 16:49.516
The director
of "dirty dancing."

16:49.518 --> 16:52.319
Okay, you wanna hear
something really crazy?

16:52.454 --> 16:54.254
I also directed
"sister act"!

16:54.389 --> 16:55.588
Get the [bleep] out.

16:55.590 --> 16:56.789
You get the [bleep] out.

16:56.791 --> 16:57.657
Damn.

16:57.792 --> 16:59.659
Gilda would
love it here.

16:59.794 --> 17:03.463
And my arm's not even tired!
This is so wild!

17:03.598 --> 17:04.931
Please wake up.

17:05.067 --> 17:06.599
We don't have to be
on the run anymore!

17:06.735 --> 17:08.134
I explained
to that mob family

17:08.270 --> 17:10.603
That I was joking about
knowing "whatever."

17:10.605 --> 17:13.139
They were surprisingly cool.
I'm sorry.

17:13.141 --> 17:14.541
This is all my fault!

17:14.676 --> 17:16.877
But if you die
and kiss my boyfriend,

17:17.012 --> 17:18.211
So help me, god...

17:18.213 --> 17:19.412
[ door opens ]

17:19.414 --> 17:20.881
Oh. Hi.

17:21.015 --> 17:22.349
I thought
you were in japan.

17:22.484 --> 17:24.217
I was. I'm back.

17:24.352 --> 17:25.953
How do you know hayley?

17:26.955 --> 17:29.089
And another thing
you can do in heaven

17:29.224 --> 17:31.691
Is come up to the screening room
and watch your favorite scene,

17:31.826 --> 17:34.827
Over and over again,
as if for the first time.

17:34.963 --> 17:36.162
[ quietly ]
it's exquisite.

17:36.298 --> 17:37.830
The armpit tickle scene?

17:37.832 --> 17:40.901
You really like that scene,
more than anyone else!

17:41.035 --> 17:42.969
But as I'm sure
you know,

17:43.105 --> 17:44.971
"dirty dancing" is a rich
and deep text,

17:45.107 --> 17:46.506
And as such,

17:46.641 --> 17:47.908
Holds different meanings
for different people.

17:48.043 --> 17:49.842
I did not know that.

17:49.978 --> 17:52.245
I thought it was just sexy
and horny and stuff.

17:52.247 --> 17:55.582
For example, you love
the armpit tickle scene,

17:55.584 --> 17:57.517
But your friend gilda
loves this scene.

17:57.652 --> 17:58.919
[ projector clicks, whirs ]

17:59.053 --> 18:01.154
<i> When I'm wrong,</i>
<i> I say I'm wrong.</i>

18:08.196 --> 18:09.896
<i>You looked wonderful out there.</i>

18:15.403 --> 18:16.469
Hayley: Oh, my god!

18:16.605 --> 18:17.870
I was totally wrong about

18:18.006 --> 18:19.539
What gilda was getting
from the movie!

18:19.674 --> 18:21.742
I finally know
how to fix things!

18:21.876 --> 18:23.343
Not ready
to go to the big

18:23.478 --> 18:26.012
"dirty dancing" screening room
in the sky just yet.

18:26.348 --> 18:28.748
[ gasps ]
she wasn't boy crazy --

18:28.883 --> 18:30.550
She was<i> man</i> crazy!

18:30.685 --> 18:32.285
About her dad!

18:32.287 --> 18:33.553
But not like that!

18:33.688 --> 18:36.222
I'm the one
who got her obsessed with boys!

18:36.224 --> 18:37.758
I met emile ardolino,

18:37.892 --> 18:40.693
And he showed me that you
can't actually care for someone

18:40.695 --> 18:42.295
If you aren't seeing them
clearly.

18:42.430 --> 18:43.696
Everything went off the rails

18:43.832 --> 18:46.166
Because I was pushing
my stuff on you.

18:46.301 --> 18:47.367
Yeah, I tried
to tell you,

18:47.502 --> 18:48.901
But you were talking
so much at the mall.

18:49.037 --> 18:50.570
You're talking a lot
now, too.

18:50.705 --> 18:52.105
Oh, good,
you're both here!

18:52.240 --> 18:53.440
Roger --
barney bux!

18:53.575 --> 18:55.108
You need
to make it right.

18:55.243 --> 18:58.444
Tell her all of the things
you never said.
Okay.

18:58.446 --> 19:00.180
Your mother...Died.

19:00.315 --> 19:01.447
Yeah, I know.

19:01.449 --> 19:02.782
How?
I figured it out.

19:02.917 --> 19:05.051
Not this!
Say the lines.

19:05.187 --> 19:08.921
Oh. I have been distant
these last 13 years.

19:09.057 --> 19:10.857
No! Say the lines
from the movie!

19:10.859 --> 19:12.192
That's where
the magic is!

19:12.327 --> 19:14.394
Can't I just say
what I feel personally?

19:14.529 --> 19:16.196
Absolutely not.

19:16.331 --> 19:19.399
Say, "when I'm wrong,
I say I'm wrong."

19:19.534 --> 19:21.934
When I'm wrong,
I say I'm wrong.

19:22.070 --> 19:24.937
Then look at your
beautiful daughter,

19:24.939 --> 19:27.874
Who is blossoming
into her own person.

19:27.876 --> 19:30.076
She's becoming a woman!

19:30.078 --> 19:31.277
You see that now.

19:31.279 --> 19:34.280
Say, "you looked
wonderful out there."

19:34.416 --> 19:35.682
Out where?
Just say it!

19:35.817 --> 19:38.150
You looked wonderful out there.

19:38.152 --> 19:44.557
♪<i> now I've had</i>
<i> the time of my life</i> ♪

19:44.559 --> 19:48.628
♪<i> and I've never felt</i>
<i> like this before</i> ♪

19:48.763 --> 19:51.231
♪<i> yes, I swear</i> ♪

19:51.366 --> 19:53.233
